reviewText: great quality dvd by the crowes again and a great performance.  the only problem is that the dts audio option hiccups when you switch between songs.  it looks like if you go to the dts option from the menu screen you should be ok.  if you switch audio when your watching the dvd, you might get this problem.  great show!!  if you're a fan, get this!
summary: great dvd but problems with dts

reviewText: VERY OUTSTANDING!!! This is a "super", outstanding concert performance by the Black Crowes, filmed on March 20, 2008, at the Wiltern Theater in Los Angeles. It features songs from their recent "WARPAINT" Album, performed "Live". Plus, as an extra bonus, you get Luther Dickinson (the lead singer/lead guitarist for the North Mississippi Allstars) playing guitar, including great slide guitar play. This concert contains 17 GREAT songs. It is great from beginning to the end. It has an approximate running time of 103 minutes.The line-up consists of the following:Chris Robinson - vocals, harmonica, guitarRich Robinson - guitar, vocalsLuther Dickinson - guitar, including great, slide guitar play.Adam MacDougal - keyboard playerSteve Gorman - drums, percussionSven Pipien - bass, vocalsCharity White - backing vocalsMona Lisa Young - backing vocalsThe song set is as follows:1. Goodbye Ye Daughters of the Revolution2. Walk Believer Walk3. Oh Josephine4. Evergreen5. Wee Who See the Deep6. Locust Street7. Movin' on Down the Line8. Wounded Bird9. God's Got It10.There's Gold in Them Hills11.Whoa Mule12.Poor Elijah/Tribute to Johnson (Medley)13.Darling of the Underground Press14.Bad Luck Blue Eyes Goodbye15.Don't Know Why16.Torn & Frayed (A Mick Jagger/Keith Richards song)17.Hey GrandmaOverall, this is an outstanding concert, showcasing the Black Crowes at their best. It's great to see Luther Dickinson in the line-up, playing guitar, including excellent slide guitar play. Rich is also a great guitarist, and Chris is great on lead vocals. The rest of the band is great also. This is a "must-have" for any Black Crowes fan, or any Southern Rock fan, or any Rock fan period!!! I'm certainly a big fan!!! I highly, gladly recommend this one. If you like rock & roll, you'll love every minute of this one!!! Thanks and Enjoy!!!
summary: The Black Crowes "Warpaint" = A Great New Concert Release!!! It Features Songs From Their Recent Album "Warpaint" = A1+!!!!!!!!!

reviewText: With that being said, this dvd is incredible, with little faults.The cinematography is absolutely brilliant.At times I felt like I was watching "The song remains the same'and 'ladies and gentlemen..'It's that good.The band does not perform like a 'band', but more like an arsenal.Luther Dickinsen (I spell that right?)does a wonderful job on guitar,making me forget about 'Mr. Ford'for a bit.Rich Robinson=PURE menace.Chris Robinson is simply put, ON POINT.My sister came in when this was on and she asked me 'Is that Jesus?'I said no, but he's got him in him.'The audio on this  is simply awesome, between the 5.1 and the stereo, this is worth repeated viewings and simply a MUST HAVE.
summary: The Greatest Rock And Roll Band In The World.

reviewText: I just received this DVD for my birthday, and it is just like seeing them live. I've seen them 4 times in the last 3 years with Luther & Adam....they make the Black Crowes better than they ever were. I love Warpaint, and this DVD gives you everything you want, including Steve Gorman as a marching band drummer on "God's Got It". You won't be disappointed...do yourself a favor and go see them live.
